narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This class is a good french class. The readings are a good level and the movies are entertaining to watch. That said, it is a lot of work, about an hour each night. If you've got to do a language class and you know some french, it works.

I would definitely recommend this class. I took the class after placing into L3 on the placement test, but after the first few days I felt like I should have been in L4. On the whole, it was a lot of review for me, and it was a pretty easy class. However, you learn a lot, and it's a great way to solidify grammar.

It's a very interesting french course because you do more than just study grammar or learn how to conjugate irregular verbs. The bulk of the course is taught through French films/texts, which makes lessons easier to learn since they are attached to a story, and also makes it much more interesting than a typical foreign language class.

I would recommend this class highly if you are ready to move beyond the typical French course and lame textbooks with uninteresting stories. This took my French to a new level and I loved the books we read and the films we watched!
